postcontent: Protocol for myself when I do sell or buy a firearm on Armslist is decernment of the person thru email or texting to begin with. Some of the listing I see they can't even spell the make or model of what they are selling.  Some cases won't give you correct info on the firearm..  For example: lnib. Low round count, but come to find out it was mfg 10-15 yrs ago. Like Glock police trade in thats been cleaned up. LolDon't get me wrong, their a few cool guy's out there that I've met.What's so hard about discussing ahead of time on how you want to do the transaction.  Everyone has their personal preference on bill of sale etc. That's good that you cover your own ass and try not to sell or buy from someone that's not legal or might not act responsible enough to have or sell one..I do bill of sale after the ftf agreement is made 1st.....then exchange ID's and then exchange cash/firearm.  I don't agree with photo Id taking because of identity theft. My preference..Oh, don't forget hotguz dot com. to check serial # if stolen. It's not connected to police records. Call local sheriff's Dept they will run serial number over phone for you. you can go as far as kbi felon registery it's free. Thanks for the heads up and have a Happy New Year to all you gun lovers.  LolHappy Trails.

title: For Sale/Trade:  2000 VW Passat 1.8T
postcontent: I have for sale or trade a 2000 VW Passat 1.8 Turbo.  It is an overall great daily driver, I just don't want to have two cars on insurance anymore.  It has 168000 miles on it.  It has minimal issues and is in great running order for its age.  This is a 5-Speed, please do not meet me if you do not know how to drive a manual.  I am asking $1550 cash OBO and $1700 trade value. (Please do not low-ball me, I don't care about any estimates from online websites.  This is a usable and nice vehicle.  You can't get a decent used car for less than $1200 anymore.) If you would like anymore info or pics, just shoot me an email.  I will now list the pro's and con's:Pros: (I'll try not to be superfluous) -No electronic issues. (Rare for a VW.)-Interior is nice (Other than headliner coming down a bit.)-AC/Heat work extremely well.-Power windows, locks, and mirrors.-5-Speed is very smooth.-Clutch is still very nice, you can tell by it being able to take off in 5th gear with no gas.  Also you can use the old parking brake test.  PLEASE DO NOT BURN OUT MY CLUTCH WHEN TESTING IT.  It is easy to slip it when you are doing high gear launches, do not do one of these tests if you are not experienced enough.  Thank you.-The Turbo allows for great acceleration and higher efficiency.-Gas mileage is about 27 average.-Large trunk space.-Previous owner was a bus mechanic and replaced many things, notably the timing belt and water pump among others.  -I replaced battery, be glad because even with my Autozone employee discount it was still $150.  -Tire tread is still great.-All lights work.-Clean title-Very smooth overall in turning, suspension, etc.-Safety is rated very well, you can google it.  Cons:-ABS/Brake lights are on to what can be deduced as several possible reasons: First, the rear pads and rotors I know need to be replaced.  Second, the ABS sensors might need to be cleaned. Third, I know the brakes need to be bled.  I haven't gotten around to fixing these issues because I am not for sure that any one of them is causing the brake light.  What I do know is that I was able to go to a dead stop from 40 MPH with even braking lines and minimal locking in very little time.  During my daily driving, I can tell the brakes are still functioning with no issues so the brake light has not been an issue for me.  You can test them when we meet.-Clear coat is pealing off in some places.-It appeared to have been side swiped at some point, you can tell in the picture.  It isn't that bad though.-I only have one key and the battery is dead on the key fob.  Meeting:  We can meet in Clarksville somewhere where you can test the brakes, clutch, and drive it around a bit.  Like I said before, you can test them but DO NOT DAMAGE THE CLUTCH OR BRAKES.  After you check it out, we will meet at the County Clerk and I will transfer ownership to you there, I do this to make sure it isn't in my name anymore and to get my plates back.  I also do a bill of sale to have a log of the sale.
